Enumeration Type Documentation

enum sbwdataBlockType
 

Datatypes used in C API.

uses standard encoding of datatypes used in both the API and in datablocks.

Enumeration values:
SBWByteType  C API type - unsigned char.
SBWIntegerType  C API type - SBWInteger.
SBWDoubleType  C API type - SBWDouble.
SBWBooleanType  C API type - SBWBoolean.
SBWStringType  C API type - char *.
SBWArrayType  C API type - <T>* or <T>**.
SBWListType  C API type - SBWDataBlockReader * or SBWDataBlockWriter *.
SBWVoidType  placeholder when no value is returned from a method.
SBWTerminateType  value of last byte in a datablock or message.
SBWErrorType  placeholder when error has occured in an API function.

Definition at line 90 of file DataBlockType.h.

enum sbwExceptionCode
 

Exception types used in C API.

uses standard encoding of exceptions used in both in the API and in exception messages.

Enumeration values:
SBWApplicationExceptionCode  generated by a module ie not raised by the SBW infastructure.
SBWRawExceptionCode  generated by a OS or unhandled exception.
SBWCommunicationExceptionCode  communication between modules has been disrupted.
SBWModuleStartExceptionCode  unable to start module when a new module instance was required.
SBWTypeMismatchExceptionCode  the data contained in a datablock doesn't correspond to the requested type.
SBWIncomptatibleMethodSignatureExceptionCode  two method signatures do not match.
SBWModuleIdSyntaxExceptionCode  the syntax of a module instance identifier string is incorrect.
SBWIncorrectCategorySyntaxExceptionCode  the syntax of a service category string is incorrect.
SBWServiceNotFoundExceptionCode  the requested service doesn't exist.
SBWMethodTypeNotBlockTypeExceptionCode  thrown during communications if a supplied class uses types which are not data block types (not raised in C++ library).
SBWMethodAmbiguousExceptionCode  the given signature matches more than one method on a service.
SBWUnsupportedObjectTypeExceptionCode  the given valid type is not supported by a client library.
SBWMethodNotFoundExceptionCode  the given signature or name doesn't match any method on a service.
SBWSignatureSyntaxExceptionCode  the syntax of the given signature is incorrect.
SBWModuleDefinitionExceptionCode  exception thrown when an attempt to define a new module fails.
SBWModuleNotFoundExceptionCode  the requested module doesn't exist.
SBWBrokerStartExceptionCode  the requested module doesn't exist.

Definition at line 65 of file DataBlockType.h.

enum sbwmoduleManagementType
 

The ways in which a given module can be managed by the broker.

Uses standard encoding used by both by the API and the broker interface.

Enumeration values:
SBW_UniqueModule  broker only creates one instance of the module and refers all requests to that instance.
SBW_SelfManagedModule  broker creates a new instance for each module instance request.

Definition at line 118 of file DataBlockType.h.

enum sbwmoduleMode
 

The modes in which a given module/application can operate with respect to SBW.

Enumeration values:
SBWNormalMode  either not connected or only consuming services.
SBWModuleMode  providing services.
SBWRegisterMode  registering services.
